# Website to MDC Conversion Rules

## Overview
This document outlines a comprehensive methodology for analyzing websites and converting them into structured MDC (Markdown Cursor) format. The process involves multiple phases of discovery, analysis, and documentation.

## Target Website
- **URL**: `https://xx.wearemotto.com/`
- **Status**: Protected by Cloudflare (requires JavaScript-enabled browser)
- **Access Method**: Browser automation required (Puppeteer/Playwright)

## Phase 1: Website Access and Discovery

### 1.1 URL Validation
- Verify URL accessibility
- Check HTTP status codes
- Identify protection mechanisms (Cloudflare, WAF, etc.)
- Handle authentication if required

### 1.2 Technology Detection
- **Frontend Framework**: Detect React, Vue, Angular, Next.js, etc.
- **CSS Framework**: Identify Tailwind, Bootstrap, Material-UI, etc.
- **Build Tools**: Webpack, Vite, Parcel indicators
- **Analytics**: Google Analytics, Segment, etc.
- **CDN**: Cloudflare, CloudFront, etc.

### 1.3 Sitemap Discovery
- Check `/sitemap.xml`
- Check `/robots.txt` for sitemap references
- Analyze navigation structure
- Identify all routes/pages
- Map internal linking structure

### 1.4 Page Inventory
Create a comprehensive list of:
- Homepage
- All navigation pages
- Dynamic routes
- API endpoints (if accessible)
- Static assets structure

## Phase 2: Multi-Pass Design Analysis

### Pass 1: Visual Structure Mapping
- **Layout Hierarchy**: Document header, footer, sidebar, main content areas
- **Grid Systems**: CSS Grid, Flexbox, custom grid implementations
- **Typography**: Font families, sizes, weights, line heights, color schemes
- **Color Palette**: Primary, secondary, accent colors, gradients
- **Spacing System**: Margin/padding patterns, rhythm
- **Component Structure**: Reusable UI components identified

### Pass 2: Interactive Elements and Behaviors
- **Buttons**: Styles, states (hover, active, disabled), variants
- **Forms**: Input types, validation patterns, error states
- **Navigation**: Menu types, dropdown behaviors, mobile menu
- **Modals/Dialogs**: Trigger mechanisms, animations, close behaviors
- **Tooltips**: Positioning, triggers, content patterns
- **Accordions/Tabs**: Expand/collapse behaviors
- **Carousels/Sliders**: Navigation controls, autoplay, indicators

### Pass 3: Responsive Design Analysis
- **Breakpoints**: Mobile, tablet, desktop breakpoints
- **Mobile-First vs Desktop-First**: Approach identification
- **Layout Changes**: How components adapt at different sizes
- **Navigation Adaptation**: Mobile menu patterns
- **Touch Interactions**: Swipe gestures, touch targets
- **Viewport Meta Tags**: Configuration

### Pass 4: Page Flow and Navigation Mapping
- **User Journeys**: Primary paths through the site
- **Navigation Patterns**: Breadcrumbs, pagination, filters
- **State Management**: URL parameters, query strings, hash routing
- **Transitions**: Page transitions, loading states
- **Error Pages**: 404, 500, etc.

## Phase 3: Design Element Extraction

### Visual Patterns
- **Icons**: Icon library (Font Awesome, Material Icons, custom SVG)
- **Images**: Formats, optimization, lazy loading patterns
- **Illustrations**: Style, placement, usage
- **Shadows**: Elevation system, depth patterns
- **Borders**: Radius patterns, border styles
- **Backgrounds**: Patterns, gradients, overlays

### Interactive Patterns
- **Hover Effects**: Transitions, transforms, color changes
- **Click Feedback**: Ripple effects, state changes
- **Loading States**: Skeletons, spinners, progress indicators
- **Empty States**: Placeholder content, call-to-action patterns
- **Success/Error States**: Toast notifications, inline messages

### Animation Patterns
- **Transitions**: Duration, easing functions
- **Keyframe Animations**: Entrance, exit, micro-interactions
- **Scroll Animations**: Parallax, fade-in, reveal effects
- **Performance**: GPU acceleration, will-change usage

### Responsive Patterns
- **Container Queries**: Usage and patterns
- **Media Queries**: Breakpoint strategies
- **Flexible Typography**: Fluid typography, clamp() usage
- **Image Responsiveness**: srcset, sizes, picture elements

## Phase 4: Code Structure Analysis

### HTML Structure
- Semantic HTML usage
- Accessibility attributes (ARIA labels, roles)
- Meta tags and SEO elements
- Schema.org markup

### CSS Architecture
- **Methodology**: BEM, SMACSS, OOCSS, etc.
- **Preprocessors**: Sass, Less, PostCSS
- **CSS-in-JS**: Styled-components, Emotion, etc.
- **Utility Classes**: Tailwind patterns, custom utilities
- **Custom Properties**: CSS variables usage

### JavaScript Patterns
- **Framework Patterns**: Component structure, hooks, state management
- **Event Handling**: Delegation, custom events
- **API Integration**: Fetch patterns, error handling
- **Performance**: Code splitting, lazy loading, memoization

## Phase 5: Content Analysis

### Content Structure
- **Headings Hierarchy**: H1-H6 usage patterns
- **Text Content**: Paragraphs, lists, blockquotes
- **Media Content**: Images, videos, embeds
- **Call-to-Actions**: Button text, placement, styling

### SEO Elements
- **Meta Tags**: Title, description, Open Graph
- **Structured Data**: JSON-LD, microdata
- **URL Structure**: Clean URLs, slugs
- **Internal Linking**: Anchor text, link density

## Phase 6: Performance Analysis

### Metrics
- **Core Web Vitals**: LCP, FID, CLS
- **Load Times**: First paint, time to interactive
- **Resource Sizes**: Images, scripts, stylesheets
- **Network Requests**: API calls, third-party scripts

### Optimization Patterns
- **Image Optimization**: Formats, compression, lazy loading
- **Code Splitting**: Route-based, component-based
- **Caching Strategies**: Service workers, HTTP caching
- **CDN Usage**: Asset delivery patterns

## Phase 7: Accessibility Analysis

### WCAG Compliance
- **Color Contrast**: Text readability
- **Keyboard Navigation**: Tab order, focus indicators
- **Screen Reader Support**: ARIA labels, semantic HTML
- **Alt Text**: Image descriptions

### Inclusive Design
- **Font Sizes**: Minimum readable sizes
- **Touch Targets**: Minimum 44x44px
- **Error Messages**: Clear, actionable feedback
- **Form Labels**: Proper association

